• CeLight, Inc. Iselin, NJ. November 2000–February 2002. Manager, Optical Telecommunication Systems Design. Member of the 5-person architecture team that is responsible for all technical aspects of a novel optical communication system architecture, interface with marketing, and strategic future planning. Hands on work and responsibility for performance evaluation, modeling and analysis of ultra-high capacity, long-haul novel optical telecommunication systems, which played a very important role in securing $45 million of second round venture capital funding. Signal propagation in optical fibers. System architecture exploration and development. Interface with the technical consultants of venture capital firms.